{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id788fd64e-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s751"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"751"},"text":"§ 751.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Personnel","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In connection with the establishment of such fish-rescue station there is authorized the following personnel, namely: One district supervisor, to have general charge of fish-rescue and fish-cultural operations in the Mississippi Valley; a superintendent, two field foremen, four fish-culturists at large, one engineer at large, one clerk, two coxswains at large, and two apprentice fish-culturists.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id788fd64f-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1922-04-28/ch153/s2"},"text":"Apr. 28, 1922, ch. 153, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/42/501"},"text":"42 Stat. 501","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id788fd650-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id788fd651-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id788fd652-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Provisions relating to the compensation of such personnel have been omitted as such pay is fixed pursuant to chapter 51 and subchapter III of chapter 53 of Title 5, Government Organization and Employees.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"id788fd653-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"id788fd654-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For transfer of functions of other officers, employees, and agencies of Department of the Interior, with certain exceptions, to Secretary of the Interior, with power to delegate, see Reorg. Plan No. 3 of 1950, §§ 1, 2, eff. ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1950-05-24"},"text":"May 24, 1950","children":[],"tail":", 15 F.R. 3174, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/1262"},"text":"64 Stat. 1262","children":[],"tail":", set out in the Appendix to Title 5, Government Organization and Employees."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
